General.Name: Doc.ai Neuron
General.Description:
NeuRoN is a decentralized artificial intelligence network. It is a distributed and permissionless network of users with data ownership necessary to train neural network models. A publicly accessible network democratizes access to artificial intelligence.

NeuRoN will function as a token-based economy. Participants will be required to prove ownership of tokens and receive tokens for participating.

ICO.Description:
NeuRoN is a decentralized artificial intelligence network. It is a distributed and permissionless network of users with data ownership necessary to train neural network models. A publicly accessible network democratizes access to artificial intelligence.

NeuRoN will function as a token-based economy. Participants will be required to prove ownership of tokens and receive tokens for participating.

Team:

  • Walter De Brouwer 
  • Sam De Brouwer 
  • Alan Greene 
  • Anthea Chung 
  • Jeremy Howard 

Doc.ai will be holding its ICO on September 28, 2017. The ICO token supply represents 37% of the total token supply, so there will be a total of 318,200,000 tokens available, for 0.094 USD each at the offering. The ICO funding cap is 30,000,000 USD and the end date is yet to be announced. The ICO can also end if the funding cap is reached.

Token Reserve Split (63%):

  • 33% For distribution to incentivize the ecosystem;
  • 30% retained by doc.ai;
